    "chatPageAssistantGreeting": "Hi! I am your AI coding assistant.\n\nI can help with:\n- Writing and refining code\n- Explaining errors\n- Reviewing and refactoring code\n- Generating unit tests\n\nWhat would you like to work on?",
    "chatPageUserDebouncePrompt": "Can you help me write a React custom Hook for debounced search?",
    "chatPageAssistantDebounceReply": "Absolutely. Here is a `useDebounceSearch` Hook:\n\n```typescript\nfunction useDebounceSearch(delay = 300) {\n  const [query, setQuery] = useState('')\n  const [debouncedQuery, setDebouncedQuery] = useState('')\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    const timer = setTimeout(() => {\n      setDebouncedQuery(query)\n    }, delay)\n    return () => clearTimeout(timer)\n  }, [query, delay])\n\n  return { query, setQuery, debouncedQuery }\n}\n```\n\n**Highlights:**\n1. Waits 300ms before triggering search\n2. Resets the timer on every keystroke\n3. Cleans up the timer on unmount",
    "chatPageAssistantDebounceThinking1": "Parse the request: debounced React Hook",
    "chatPageAssistantDebounceThinking2": "Choose `useState` and `useEffect` as the baseline",
    "chatPageAssistantDebounceThinking3": "Add cleanup to avoid timer leaks",
    "chatPageUserLoadingPrompt": "Can you add a loading state and request cancellation too?",
    "chatPageAssistantLoadingReply": "Sure. Here is an enhanced version with `loading` and `AbortController` support:\n\n```typescript\nfunction useDebounceSearch<T>(fetcher: (q: string, signal: AbortSignal) => Promise<T>, delay = 300) {\n  const [query, setQuery] = useState('')\n  const [data, setData] = useState<T | null>(null)\n  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false)\n  const abortRef = useRef<AbortController>()\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!query) { setData(null); return }\n    const timer = setTimeout(async () => {\n      abortRef.current?.abort()\n      const ctrl = new AbortController()\n      abortRef.current = ctrl\n      setLoading(true)\n      try {\n        const res = await fetcher(query, ctrl.signal)\n        if (!ctrl.signal.aborted) setData(res)\n      } finally {\n        if (!ctrl.signal.aborted) setLoading(false)\n      }\n    }, delay)\n    return () => clearTimeout(timer)\n  }, [query, delay, fetcher])\n\n  return { query, setQuery, data, loading }\n}\n```\n\n**What changed:**\n- Tracks request progress with `loading`\n- Cancels the previous in-flight request before sending a new one\n- Uses `AbortSignal` to avoid stale updates",
    "chatPageAssistantLoadingThinking1": "Extend the Hook with request lifecycle state",
    "chatPageAssistantLoadingThinking2": "Add `AbortController` for cancellation",
    "chatPageAssistantLoadingThinking3": "Prevent stale responses from overriding newer data",
    "chatPageAssistantLoadingThinking4": "Keep the generic API reusable",
